Vulvae oblong, with strong setae (
Figs 15, 16
). Operculum higher than bursa; its apex with a subtriangular incision and at least 3 or 4 setae in each of two longitudinal rows, apical setae longest. Apical part of bursa with pair of hyaline lobes. Lateral and mesal bursal sclerites together with 5–8 setae. Posterior median sclerite of bursa with 13–15 setae arranged in two rows, apical setae longest.

